challenge.challenge_prompt: Compute the sum of Euler's totient function φ(n) for all integers n from 1 to 100. Euler's totient function φ(n) counts the number of integers in the range [1, n] that are coprime with n (i.e., the greatest common divisor of the integer and n is 1). Your solution must output a single integer: the sum of φ(n) for n = 1 to 100.
